reviewText:
I published a first review about this game a few hours ago. Maybe it wasn't clear for some people previously, so I'll try again to make them understand better about my opinion on this game:

As a Worms Ultimate Mayhem player, I was curious about this WWPR and I purchased it to find out if it's a good Worms. The thing is, I couldn't have gone far enough. Why? Probably not because of the game itself, which seems quite feature-rich and fun for some players here. I requested (and obtained) a refund because of the so-called remastering we've been promised. I think it is just some kind of emulation of the old game, with some tweaks to ensure it works on the latest Windows:

1-Menus and UI (in Menus) aren't upscaled, they are stuck to default resolution from back then when the game was released for the first time;
2-There's no Windowed mode (I guess it wasn't available in the first release either, but for a remaster, we could have expected to see such a basic" feature available on day one);
3-Alt+Tab should be avoided with this game (I was stuck once
